    │ Help: dot-prefixed names declare local labels; add the trailing ':' (e.g. `.exit:`)
    │ 
    │ Note: K65 local labels start with '.' and end with ':'. Without the ':' the parser treats the dot-prefixed identifier as an instruction mnemonic, which is then reported here. References like `goto .label` will fail separately as undefined symbols until the label is declared correctly.
